Joint parliament legal affairs committee co chairman Muturi Kigano says the country must brace itself for a referendum&nbsp;courtesy of article 255 of the constitution.&nbsp;This is because the BBI constitutional referendum bill before parliament seeks to alter the governance structure and that of parliament and therefore people&rsquo;s sovereignty and they must have their say.&nbsp;However, even as parliament leadership prepares for a possible special sitting to dispense with the BBI bill, lack of financial resources to fund the exercise remains a major headache.